dialogue: Hi.
Yes. Are you one of the retarded cousins?
Hi, nice to meet you. Kate Miller.
Oh, yeah. I love Jennifer Van Murray’s work. She’s so brilliantly incisive when it comes to deconstructing the psyche of the American middle class.
Where do I know you from?
No, that’s not it. So, you’re a soap actor? Well this must be pretty exciting for you to be in a real play, hmm?
That info-mercial! For the milk carton spout thing! You’re-you’re-you’re the guy that doesn’t know how to pour milk!!
Right, at the end, you choked on a cookie.
Happy?! Is that what I’m supposed to be Vic? Happy?
I have a question about this scene.
Well, I don’t understand why Adrienne’s attracted to Victor.
I think my character’s gonna need a little bit more of reason than that.
It doesn’t say that in the script.
Happy?! Is that what I’m supposed to be Vic? Happy?
Well, that was ah...
Yeah! Yeah, it was definitely an improvement. G’night.
Yeah?
Hmm?
Umm.
Yep.
Yeah.
So umm, I’ll see you tomorrow, huh?
Morning.
He happens to be brilliant. Which is more than I can say for that sweater you’re dating.
I don’t care. Why, do you want me to care?
Do you?
I’ve got no reason to stay.
I can’t believe we go on in, in a week.
Yeah, I guess. Look, what are we gonna do about this scene, huh?
Well umm, maybe if it had more heat.
Well, Adrian’s looking for a reason to stay, right? Victor can’t just kiss her, he’s gotta, gotta really give her a reason, y'know?
Or maybe, maybe he could grab her, and, and, and, and lift her up.
And then she could rip off his shirt and kiss his chest, and, and his stomach!
And then right, right when the scene ends, he could take her with this raw, animal....
Yeah, that’s pretty much what I had in mind.
Hi.
About what?
Nooo. And there’s really no reason he should find out, so ah let’s not make a big deal about it, okay?
Look umm, I, I was, I was just caught up in the moment. That’s all it was. Joey, I’m-I’m sorry you feel bad, but haven’t you ever sleep with a women where it meant more to her than it did to you?
Hi, Lauren.
Fabulous.
Become a drama critic!
By the way, he dumped me tonight after he read my review.
Yep! I sure know how to pick ‘em, huh? Y'know I gave up a part on a soap for this!
Really. What?
Why the Post?
No. You?
Oh, you’re sweet and cute.
What?
What? So you never went out with an actress before?
Of course I do.
I don’t know! I just, just do this! I-I always have to pick the like the smartest guy, or-or the most talented guy… Why can’t I just pick someone like you?
Joey!
I’m soo glad I caught you, I couldn’t find you before.
They still want me for General Hospital.
Last night was wonderful. But I-I can’t stay here just for you.
I’m sorry.
Flight’s in an hour. I-I gotta go.
